The paper introduces a new agent architecture for autonomous control with a focus on verification methods. This falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) as it deals with agent-based systems. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of probabilistic models for verification, which is a common topic in Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA). The paper also mentions the simplification of the architecture for easier design-time and run-time verification, which falls under the category of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) and Software Engineering (cs.SE), respectively. Finally, the paper discusses the use of the agent architecture for complete modelling of the environment, which falls under the category of Systems and Control (cs.SY).
